From email to Joel; description how the stuff works now:

@Idempotent  default reconnection mechanism, tries to reconnect 3 times to server. (behavior can be changed very easily)

@Idempotent({@IdempotentStrategy(TimeStrategy.class)} )  such annotation will stop reconnection after 5 seconds.

@Idempotent({@IdempotentStrategy(value = TimeStrategy.class, parameter = 10)})  such annotation will stop reconnection after 10 seconds.

@Idempotent({@IdempotentStrategy(value = TimeStrategy.class, parameter = 10),@IdempotentStrategy(value = CountStrategy.class, parameter = 5)})  such annotation will try to connect to server 5 times or 10 seconds.

@Idempotent({@IdempotentStrategy(value = WaitStrategy.class, parameter = 2), @IdempotentStrategy(value = CountStrategy.class, parameter = 5)})  such annotation will try to connect to server 5 times and will wait 2 seconds between reconnection.

Common mechanism can be specified for whole class by specifying the idempotent annotation for the class, each method can override the default reconnection mechanism by specifying it's own idempotent annotation.

Currently the IProjectContainerManager was modify that each call to the server will use default reconnection mechanism, with one exception, the checkConnection method has override the Idempotent in such way that reconnection will not be performed.

By default no reconnection is done.
But currently ProjectContainerManager is configured as follows:

@Idempotent({
	// try to reconnect 3 times.
	@IdempotentStrategy(value=CountStrategy.class, parameter=3),
	// wait 2 seconds between reconnections.
	@IdempotentStrategy(value=WaitStrategy.class, parameter=2)
})

It means try to reconnect three times with two second delay between reconnection.

